  "text": "A 20-year-old woman developed ataxia, extrapyramidal movements, myoclonus, and progressive dementia.\nBrain biopsy disclosed status spongiosus, diagnostic of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease; this is the youngest spontaneous case ever reported.\nCreutzfeldt-Jakob disease can occur in young adulthood.",
